g.text: ●​Exercise7,p.163Thomas​●​Searchsomethingfrom"Thomas"andexplainhowyouwillusethisinyourclassroomorhowyouwillhavea​colleagueuseit.​○​AtfirstIdidnotfindanypossiblewaythatThomascouldbeusefulinacorporate​training/HigherEdITsetting.ButthenIdidsomesearchesforHigherEducationtechnology​billsandfoundsomeinterestingbillsaboutimmigrationandhowtocreateopportunitiesfor​innovativeandeducatedimmigrants.Whilethisdoesn’tdirectlyapplytoanythingIcurrently​do,itwouldpossiblybenecessarythatonedaymydepartmenthastoteachabouttechnology​toimmigrantswhomayexcelinotherareasofbusiness,butneedtechnologyhelpbecauseof​theirlimitedexperiencewithit.TheThomassiteisgoodforlookingatwhatmightbecoming​intermsoflaws,andwhatsomeofthetrendsinCongressmaybe.​ReturntoQuestion1.HowlongdidittaketoreceiveyouritemfromInterlibraryLoan?​Stillhavenotreceivedit.​10.​Reread the Libraries Online and Access to Proprietary Databases. Describe how you would teach the​importance of having access to your regional library system, how to obtain it, the potential resources available​through your own school, and special access to sites like the Library of Congress to your students or your​colleagues (if your students are too young). Be sure to lead with your objective and focus more on the content​than the pedagogy in your explanation.
